  {
    "name": "listMaterializedViews",
    "title": "List Materialized Views",
    "description": "List all materialized views in the `public` schema of a PostgreSQL database. Unlike regular views, materialized views store their results physically and must be refreshed explicitly.\n\n<usecase>\nUse when:\n- Exploring a database for stored aggregates that may be stale\n- Auditing which materialized views require refresh scheduling\n- The user asks what materialized views exist\n</usecase>\n\n<examples>\nâś“ \"What materialized views are in mydb?\" â†’ listMaterializedViews(database=\"mydb\")\nâś“ \"Does an mv_recent_orders materialized view exist?\" â†’ listMaterializedViews to check\nâś— \"List regular views\" â†’ use listViews instead\n</examples>\n\n<what_it_returns>\nA sorted JSON array of materialized-view name strings.\n</what_it_returns>\n\n<pagination>\nPaginated. Pass the prior response's `nextCursor` as `cursor` to fetch the next page.\n</pagination>",
    "inputSchema": {
      "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
      "description": "Request for the `listMaterializedViews` tool.",
